<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h1>Tutorial 25. Finishing the Bottom of the Slit and the Hem of the Dress.</h1>
<p><strong>First I will finish the slit and then hem the dress with the lining.</strong> I stitch at a presser-foot width from the edge.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I will gradually narrow down the seam allowance starting 7-8cm before the end of the slit</strong> to make sure its edges will eventually meet in the corner at the top. I put the two edges of the slit together and mark the point where I will start narrowing the seam allowance.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I sew over the face side because the edges of the slit must look particularly neat here. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I reach the point where I need to start narrowing down the seam allowance. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I select a smaller stitch length and continue sewing trying to arrive right at the apex of the slit.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I turn the piece about the needle and sew along the other side of the slit down to the marked point, gradually expanding the seam allowance back to its initial width.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image012.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I examine the top of the slit.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I continue sewing down to the end of the slit and finish at a presser foot width from the edge.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>After examining the top of the slit one more time, I noticed that the two edges don't meet in the very middle of the corner.</strong> I will re-stitch the top of the slit starting from the point where I started narrowing down the seam allowance and then remove the old stitches. I secure the face and the lining with a pin at the top of the slit to prevent them from shifting against each other.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image024.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image026.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image030.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The result looks a lot better than before.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image032.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I remove the old stitches. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image034.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Before notching the corner of the slit, I smear it with Gutermann glue from either side.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image036.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image038.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I will topstitch the seam while waiting for the glue to set.</strong> I remove the pins and roll the seam to the side of the lining (i.e. fold the seam allowance toward the lining).</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image042.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image044.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Then I topstitch the seam along the other side of the slit.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image046.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image048.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image050.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I make a row of stay-stitches along the bottom edge of the dress.</strong> I start from the princess seam and keep sewing just above the selvage from the side of the lining until I reach the slit.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image052.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image054.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I put the edges of the slit together, align their bottom edges with the main layer of the face, and continue sewing.</strong> I stop when I reach the princess seam.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image056.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image058.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image060.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I turn the piece around and continue sewing over the thicker face side</strong> (the stitches are more even in this case). I gradually bring the seam allowance to 1.2cm.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image062.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image064.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image066.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image068.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image070.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image072.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I trim all seam allowances except for those in the train area. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image074.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image076.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>And I topstitch the seam folding the seam allowance toward the lining.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image078.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image080.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image082.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Then I trim the seam allowance along the bottom edge on the other half of the dress and topstitch the seam folding the seam allowance toward the lining.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image084.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image086.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image088.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image090.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I carefully notch the top corner of the slit and stretch it. This will help me turn out the dress. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image092.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image094.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image096.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Here is what it looks like when the slit is finished with the lining: </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image098.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I turn out the bottom of the dress and carefully spread out the corners.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image100.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The hem of the train is finished as per usual:</strong> you can serge it and then fold it, glue it in place, or trim it with a soldering iron.</p>
<p><strong>I need to press the garment now.</strong> I carefully press the central seam at the back of the lining, the top of the dress, the straps, the slit, and the hem.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image102.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image104.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image106.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image108.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image110.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image112.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image114.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image116.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image118.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image120.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image122.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image124.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image126.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image128.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image130.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image132.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image134.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image136.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image138.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>The final pressing steps will be made a little later (on the eve of the photo shoot / delivery date).</p>
<p><strong>All I need to do now is secure the neckline and the halter-neck straps with blind hand stitches and finish the hem of the train.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2025_files/image140.jpg" alt=""></p>

